  "title": "SCM Executive (6 months contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Inventory &amp; Supply Planning</strong></p>\n<p>Monitor demand and plan supply requirements accurately</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Organize and conduct inventory and forecast meetings with the Project Manager</li>\n  <li>Analyze data and prepare draft forecast submissions</li>\n  <li>Finalize and submit accurate forecast data</li>\n  <li>Maintain and update forecasts in procurement systems</li>\n  <li>Set forecast limits and approve submissions accordingly</li>\n  <li>Monitor slow-moving items and take corrective actions to meet targets</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Plan proactively to maintain optimal inventory levels</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Implement processes to track inventory levels across all product lines, both short- and long-term</li>\n  <li>Monitor and evaluate Days of Supply (DOS) and forecast accuracy</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Coordinate supply chain operations to support Singapore and regional offices</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Align processes across internal and external stakeholders for better visibility of customer demand, supply plans, production, and materials in transit</li>\n  <li>Process procurement data on a weekly basis</li>\n  <li>Optimize drop shipment processes according to business rules</li>\n  <li>Generate and process purchase orders as required</li>\n  <li>Receive, update, and manage product pricing in SAP</li>\n  <li>Resolve missing pricing issues with the Product Manager, coordinate price revisions with Japan HQ, and manage price file approval and release</li>\n  <li>Execute SAP transactional operations</li>\n  <li>Download and review weekly shipping outbound schedules, and dispatch delivery schedules</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Stock Allocation Management</strong></p>\n<p>Manage allocation of stock based on forecast, additional requests, and surplus inventory to sales companies</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform weekly stock allocation to sales companies for outgoing shipments</li>\n  <li>Respond promptly to inquiries and additional stock requests from sales companies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
